K

KDPoint - Class in edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils
KDPoint is a class that represents a k-dimensional point in Euclidean space, where k is a positive integer.
KDPoint() - Constructor for class edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils.KDPoint
Default constructor initializes this as a 2D KDPoint describing the Cartesian origin.
KDPoint(int) - Constructor for class edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils.KDPoint
Initialize a k-dimensional KDPoint at the origin of the axes.
KDPoint(double...) - Constructor for class edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils.KDPoint
Initialize a KDPoint with some values.
KDPoint(KDPoint) - Constructor for class edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils.KDPoint
Initialize a KDPoint based on an already existing KDPoint.

KNNComparator<T extends KDPoint> - Class in edu.umd.cs.datastructures.projectskeletons.kdtree.utils
KNNComparator is a Serializable Comparator used for sorting KDPoints based on the KDPoint.distance(KDPoint, KDPoint) to an anchor KDPoint.
